  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 8fbeeb9dfd308426da67b82545b339a0, type: 3}
  m_Name: Mushroom_20_Wendlight
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::Hollowfen.Data.MushroomFieldGuideData
  _id: wendlight
  _commonName: Wendlight
  _latinName: Psilocybe semilanceata
  _edibility: 2
  _edibilityLabel: Psychoactive
  _description: 'Sable''s seedbook name for the Liberty Cap (Psilocybe semilanceata) — a small, slender mushroom of damp pasture, potent with psilocybin. The old hand called it Wendlight for the thin watery shine of its cap in low autumn light; it favours the wet ground a river leaves behind.'
  _idFeatures:
  - Bell or conical cap with a sharp pointed nipple (umbo) at the top
  - Cap small (5 to 25mm), tan to chestnut when moist, paler when dry
  - Dark brown to purple-black gills
  - Long, slender, pale, often slightly wavy stem
  - Bruises blue or blue-green where handled — diagnostic for psilocybin
  _habitat: Damp grassy meadows and pastures, especially grazed land. Never directly on dung.
  _season: Autumn, typically September through November in temperate regions
  _lookalikes: Deadly Galerina species contain the same liver toxins as the Death Cap and do NOT bruise blue. Conocybe and Pholiotina species can also be deadly. The blue-bruise reaction is the safest single indicator, confirmed with other features.
  _notes: 'Psychoactive and, in many places, illegal to possess. Easy to confuse with deadly Galerina when it is not bruised — never collect by appearance alone. Sable''s hand underlines the habitat once: where water had been betrayed.'
  _photo: {fileID: 21300000, guid: 2ee3be24c4dae4c2180158e9f017bd0d, type: 3}
  _photoCredit: Wikimedia Commons
  _worldPrefab: {fileID: 5716283212947672387, guid: cadc54d2a332f4134876f80e70efbdcf, type: 3}
  _displayNameId: mushroom.wendlight.name
  _descriptionId: mushroom.wendlight.description
